{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id52a6ffc9-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6","identifier":"/us/usc/t28/s1413"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1413"},"text":"§ 1413.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Venue of cases under chapter 5 of title 3","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Notwithstanding the preceding provisions of this chapter, a civil action under section 1346(g) may be brought in the United States district court for the district in which the employee is employed or in the United States District Court for the District of Columbia.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id52a6ffca-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":"(Added ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/331/s3/b/2/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–331, § 3(b)(2)(A)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1996-10-26"},"text":"Oct. 26, 1996","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/110/4069"},"text":"110 Stat. 4069","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id52a6ffcb-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id52a6ffcc-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"codification","id":"id52a6ffcd-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Codification","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/331/s3/b/2/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–331, § 3(b)(2)(A)","children":[],"tail":", which directed the amendment of chapter 37 of this title by adding thi